The state of the art media filter removes 99.9% of odor, parasites, bacteria, and viruses for safe, clean, good tasting water on the go. The large 2 1/2” filter area means better purification and increased flow. Unlike regular carbon filters, there is no need to flush the media filter before use. Replace filter every 200-250 full bottles, or about 3 months. Do not wash filter with soap. Fill only with tap water.

HOW IT WORKS

The filter’s electrically-charged membrane contains eight microns of a unique Powdered Activated Carbon (PAC) that is encapsulated within the fibers of the filter paper. It attracts negatively charged particles, including microorganisms as well as silica and heavy metals, while leaving positive minerals such as fluoride. Because the pore size of the filter is only 2 microns, it significantly reduces microbial cysts such as cryptosporidium.
